Where do all the clusters map in Cluster 1?

Load libraries.

library(Seurat)
library(tidyverse)
library(RColorBrewer)

Load umap of cluster.

load("/Volumes/all_ssd/20220414-seurat/flox-integr-res-0.0120/flox-1-res-0.074/umap-by-cluster-flox-1-res-0.074.Robj")
umap.1 <- clust.umap
umap.1$cluster.cluster <- as.character(clust.umap$cluster.cluster)
head(umap.1)
table(umap.1$cluster.cluster)

 1.1  1.2  1.3  1.4  1.5 
8302 7462 5139 2280 1961

Load umap of subclusters.

load("/Volumes/all_ssd/20220414-seurat/flox-integr-res-0.0120/flox-1-res-0.074/flox-1.1-res-0.052/umap-by-cluster-flox-1.1-res-0.052.Robj")
umap.1.1 <- clust.umap
load("/Volumes/all_ssd/20220414-seurat/flox-integr-res-0.0120/flox-1-res-0.074/flox-1.2-res-0.104/umap-by-cluster-flox-1.2-res-0.104.Robj")
umap.1.2 <- clust.umap
load("/Volumes/all_ssd/20220414-seurat/flox-integr-res-0.0120/flox-1-res-0.074/flox-1.3-res-0.056/umap-by-cluster-flox-1.3-res-0.056.Robj")
umap.1.3 <- clust.umap

Recode cluster into subclusters.

umap.1[as.vector(rownames(umap.1.1 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "1.1.1"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "1.1.1"
umap.1[as.vector(rownames(umap.1.1 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "1.1.2"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "1.1.2"
umap.1[as.vector(rownames(umap.1.2 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "1.2.1"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "1.2.1"
umap.1[as.vector(rownames(umap.1.2 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "1.2.2"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "1.2.2"
umap.1[as.vector(rownames(umap.1.2 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "1.2.3"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "1.2.3"
umap.1[as.vector(rownames(umap.1.2 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "1.2.4"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "1.2.4"
umap.1[as.vector(rownames(umap.1.3 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "1.3.1"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "1.3.1"
umap.1[as.vector(rownames(umap.1.3 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "1.3.2"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "1.3.2"
umap.1$cluster.cluster <- factor(umap.1$cluster.cluster, levels = c("1.1.1", "1.1.2", "1.2.1", "1.2.2", "1.2.3", "1.2.4", "1.3.1", "1.3.2", "1.4", "1.5"))
table(umap.1$cluster.cluster)

1.1.1 1.1.2 1.2.1 1.2.2 1.2.3 1.2.4 1.3.1 1.3.2   1.4   1.5 
 8020   282  2571  1840  1649  1402  2580  2559  2280  1961

Generate label umap.

umap.label <- umap.1 %>% group_by(cluster.cluster) %>% summarize(umap.1 = median(umap.1), umap.2 = median(umap.2))

Generate cluster umap.

cluster.umap <- ggplot() +
geom_point(data = sample(umap.1), mapping = aes(x = umap.1, y = umap.2, color = cluster.cluster), shape = 20, stroke = 0, size = 0.5) +
geom_text(data = umap.label, mapping = aes(x = umap.1, y = umap.2, label = cluster.cluster), size = 2.3) +
labs(title = "Cluster 1, Nipbl Flox/+", x = "UMAP 1", y = "UMAP 2", color = "Cluster") +
  guides(color = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = 2.3))) +
theme_classic(base_size = 7) +
theme(axis.line = element_blank(), axis.ticks = element_blank(), axis.text = element_blank(), plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 7), legend.key.size = unit(7, "pt"))
cluster.umap

clust.umap <- umap.1
save(clust.umap, file = "/Volumes/all_ssd/20220414-seurat/flox-integr-res-0.0120/flox-1-res-0.074/umap-by-cluster-flox-1-res-0.074-10.Robj")
ggsave(plot = cluster.umap, filename = "/Volumes/all_ssd/20220414-seurat/flox-integr-res-0.0120/flox-1-res-0.074/umap-by-cluster-flox-1-res-0.074-10.png", device = "png", width = 3.5, height = 2.25, units = "in")
